{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "We need agencies that cross borders to protect coastal environments.", "abstract": "Op-Ed article by Prof Ted Steinberg argues that for all its problems, the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey presents an excellent example of interstate cooperation that could prove invaluable in combating climate change; holds that increasing urbanization in coastal areas has been devastating to estuaries and wetlands, and has aggravated the danger posed by coastal flooding; calls on Port Authority to become an international leader in combating these trends.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "25", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Ted", "role": "reported", "lastname": "STEINBERG", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By TED STEINBERG", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/06/17/opinion/can-the-port-authority-save-the-planet.html", "lead_paragraph": "We need agencies that cross borders to protect coastal environments.", "headline": {"main": "Can the Port Authority Save the Planet?", "print_headline": "Can the Port Authority Save the Planet?", "content_kicker": "Op-Ed Contributor", "kicker": "Op-Ed Contributor"}, "_id": "539f885e38f0d81b22b2c109", "word_count": "819", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2014/06/17/opinion/0617OPEDmembrillas/0617OPEDmembrillas-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2014/06/17/opinion/0617OPEDmembrillas/0617OPEDmembrillas-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 447, "url": "images/2014/06/17/opinion/0617OPEDmembrillas/0617OPEDmembrillas-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/06/17/opinion/0617OPEDmembrillas/0617OPEDmembrillas-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "447"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2014/06/17/opinion/0617OPEDmembrillas/0617OPEDmembrillas-thu